{{Infobox dam | name = Bratsberg Hydroelectric Power Station | name_official = ''Bratsberg kraftverk'' | image = Bratsberg kraftverk.JPG | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Norway | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | location_map_alt = | coordinates = {{coord|63|22|23|N|10|24|27|E|region:NO_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | country = [[Norway]] | location = Sør-Trøndelag County, [[Trondheim]], Norway | purpose = | status = O | construction_began = | opening = | demolished = | cost = | owner = [[Statkraft]] | operator = | dam_type = | dam_crosses = | dam_height = | dam_height_foundation= | dam_height_thalweg = | dam_length = | dam_elevation_crest = | dam_width_crest = | dam_width_base = | dam_volume = | spillway_count = | spillway_type = | spillway_capacity = | res_name = Selbusjøen reservoir | res_capacity_total = | res_capacity_active = | res_capacity_inactive= | res_catchment = | res_surface = | res_max_length = | res_max_width = | res_max_depth = | res_elevation = | res_tidal_range = | plant_name = | plant_coordinates = | plant_operator = | plant_commission = 1977 | plant_decommission = | plant_type = C | plant_hydraulic_head = 147 | plant_turbines = 2 ([[Francis_turbine|Francis]]) | plant_capacity = 124 [[Megawatt|MW]] | plant_annual_gen = 650 [[GWh]] | plant_capacity_factor = 59.8%<!-- 650,000 MWh/year / ( 124 MW * 365 days/year * 24h/day) = 0.598 --> | website = | extra = }}
'''Bratsberg Power Station ''' (''Bratsberg kraftverk'') is a [[hydroelectricity|hydroelectric]] [[power station]] located in [[Trondheim]] in [[Sør-Trøndelag]] County, Norway, owned by [[Statkraft]]. It operates at an installed capacity of {{nowrap|124 [[Megawatt|MW]]}}, with an average annual production of 650&nbsp;GWh.<ref name=snl>{{cite encyclopedia |title=Bratsberg kraftverk |first=Knut A |last=Rosvold |encyclopedia=[[Store norske leksikon]]|editor=Henriksen, Petter |publisher=Kunnskapsforlaget |location=Oslo|url=http://www.snl.no/Bratsberg_kraftverk |language=Norwegian|accessdate=20 August 2011}}</ref> The power plant is fed from the Selbusjøen reservoir, connected with a 12&nbsp;km long tunnel, offering a gross head of 147&nbsp;m. The power plant has two Francis turbines.<ref>{{cite web | title=Bratsberg | publisher=Statkraft | url=http://www.statkraft.com/energy-sources/Power-plants/Norway/Bratsberg/ | accessdate=2015-03-13}}</ref>
