{{Infobox power station | name = El Dabaa Nuclear Power Plant | name_official = محطة الضبعة للطاقة النووية | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | location_map_alt = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord| | |region:??_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | country = Egypt | location = [[El Dabaa]], [[northern coast of Egypt|North Coast]] | status = P | construction_began = | commissioned = 2026 (''expected'')<ref name="Reuters">{{cite news|last1=Alsharif|first1=Asma|title=Russia to lend Egypt $25 billion to build nuclear power plant|url=https://www.reuters.com/article/us-egypt-russia-nuclear-idUSKCN0YA1G5|accessdate=15 May 2017|work=[[Reuters]]|date=19 May 2017|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170516193807/http://www.reuters.com/article/us-egypt-russia-nuclear-idUSKCN0YA1G5|archivedate=16 May 2017|df=}}</ref><ref>http://www.rosatom.ru/production/design/stroyashchiesya-aes/</ref> | decommissioned = | cost = US$28.75&nbsp;billion<ref>{{cite web |title=El Dabaa Nuclear Power Plant |url=https://www.power-technology.com/projects/el-dabaa-nuclear-power-plant/ |website=Power Technology |accessdate=10 October 2018}}</ref> | owner = | operator = | np_reactor_type = [[VVER#VVER-1200|VVER-1200]] | np_reactor_supplier = [[Rosatom]] | np_fuel_type = | np_fuel_supplier = | np_cogeneration = yes | np_cooling_source = [[Mediterranean Sea]] | np_cooling_towers = | ps_units_operational = | ps_units_manu_model = | ps_units_uc = | ps_units_planned = 4 × 1,200&nbsp;[[Megawatt|MW]] | ps_units_cancelled = | ps_units_decommissioned= | ps_thermal_capacity = | ps_heating_capacity = | ps_electrical_capacity = 4,800 | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | ps_storage_hours = | ps_annual_generation = | ps_annual_gen_year = | website = | extra = }}
'''El Dabaa Nuclear Power Plant''' is the first [[nuclear power plant]] planned for Egypt and will be located at [[El Dabaa]], [[Matrouh Governorate]], Egypt, which is about 130 Kilometers northwest of [[Cairo]].<ref name="Contract">{{cite news|last1=Essam El-Din|first1=Gamal|title='Egypt and Russia to sign contract for Dabaa nuclear power station very soon,' says MP|url=http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/263003/Egypt/Politics-/Egypt-and-Russia-to-sign-contract-for-Dabaa-nuclea.aspx|accessdate=15 May 2017|work=english.ahram.org.eg|agency=[[Al-Ahram]]|date=15 April 2017|language=en|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170425125751/http://english.ahram.org.eg/NewsContent/1/64/263003/Egypt/Politics-/Egypt-and-Russia-to-sign-contract-for-Dabaa-nuclea.aspx|archivedate=25 April 2017|df=}}</ref> The plant will have four [[VVER#VVER-1200|VVER-1200]] reactors, making Egypt the only country in the region to have a [[Generation III+ reactor]].<ref name="Herzliya">{{cite web|last1=Shay|first1=Shaul|title=The Egypt – Russia nuclear deal|url=http://www.herzliyaconference.org/_Uploads/dbsAttachedFiles/Egypt_nuclear_plant2015(1).pdf|website=[[Herzliya Conference]]|accessdate=15 May 2017|date=November 2015|deadurl=no|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170729231345/http://www.herzliyaconference.org/_Uploads/dbsAttachedFiles/Egypt_nuclear_plant2015%281%29.pdf|archivedate=29 July 2017|df=}}</ref><ref name=wnn-20171211/>
==History== On November 19, 2015 Egypt and Russia signed an initial agreement, under which Russia will build and finance Egypt’s first nuclear power plant.<ref name="Herzliya" /> In November 2017 preliminary contracts for the construction of four [[VVER-1200]] units were signed in the presence of Egyptian President [[Abdel Fattah el-Sisi]] and Russian President [[Vladimir Putin]].<ref name=wnn-20171211>{{cite news |url=http://www.world-nuclear-news.org/NN-Notice-to-proceed-contracts-signed-for-El-Dabaa-1112178.html |title='Notice to proceed' contracts signed for El Dabaa |publisher=World Nuclear News |date=11 December 2017 |accessdate=12 December 2017}}</ref>
==Finance== The project will cost US$28.75&nbsp;billion of which Russia will finance 85% as a state loan of US$25&nbsp;billion and Egypt will provide the remaining 15% in the form of installments. The Russian loan has a repayment period of 13 years, with an annual interest rate of 3%.<ref name="Reuters" /><ref>{{cite news|last1=Farag|first1=Mohamed|title=Electricity ministry to hold popular conference announcing details of Dabaa nuclear plant|url=http://www.dailynewsegypt.com/2017/02/12/615252/|accessdate=15 May 2017|work=[[Daily News Egypt]]|date=12 February 2017|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170212142607/http://www.dailynewsegypt.com/2017/02/12/615252/|archivedate=12 February 2017|df=}}</ref>
