The '''orthobaric density''' of a compound is the [[density]] of coexisting [[phase (matter)|phases]] ([[liquid]], [[gas]], or [[solid]]) at a given [[temperature]].
==Liquid - Gas Equilibrium== For any temperature below the [[critical point (thermodynamics)|critical point]], the density of the gas will be less than that of the liquid. At the critical point, the density of the liquid and gas phases are identical and the compound becomes a [[supercritical fluid]].<ref>McQuarrie, Donald A. and Siman, John D., ''Physical Chemistry: A Molecular Approach''. Sausalito: University Science Books, 1997.</ref>
